{
  "$schema": "https://developer.microsoft.com/json-schemas/fabric/item/dataAgent/definition/dataSource/1.0.0/schema.json",
  "artifactId": "d4000004-0004-0004-0004-000000000020",
  "workspaceId": "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000",
  "dataSourceInstructions": "PayerAnalytics is a Direct Lake semantic model over lh_gold_curated, scoped to the revenue-cycle / CFO persona. It exposes pre-defined DAX measures for denials, collections, days-in-AR, appeals, payer mix, and member economics. PREFER measures over raw SQL aggregations.\n\nQUERY LANGUAGE: DAX via EVALUATE / SUMMARIZECOLUMNS / CALCULATETABLE. NOT SQL.\n\n=== CRITICAL: TABLES YOU MAY USE (backed by Delta in lh_gold_curated) ===\nfact_claim, fact_encounter, fact_prescription, fact_diagnosis,\nagg_appeal_outcomes, agg_days_in_ar, agg_medication_adherence, agg_readmission_by_date, agg_revenue_by_drg,\ndim_payer, dim_patient, dim_provider, dim_diagnosis, dim_medication, dim_sdoh, dim_date\n\n=== DO NOT QUERY THESE TABLES \u00c3\u00a2\u00e2\u201a\u00ac\u00e2\u20ac\u009d TMDL definitions exist but Delta backing has NOT been deployed yet ===\nfact_appeal, fact_authorization, fact_capitation, fact_premium,\nagg_hedis_compliance, agg_mlr_by_payer_month, agg_raf_score, agg_star_rating, agg_star_rating_overall,\nbridge_provider_contract, dim_plan\nIf a user asks for HEDIS / MLR / RAF / Star Ratings / authorizations / capitation / premium / plan-level questions, respond that those data sources are not yet available in this environment and suggest the closest backed alternative (e.g., denial rate by payer for revenue questions).\n\n=== KEY MEASURES ===\n\nfact_claim (the workhorse table for the CFO):\n- [Total Claims], [Total Billed], [Total Paid], [Collection Rate], [Net Collection Rate]\n- [Denial Rate], [Provider Denial Count], [Avg Denial Risk], [High Risk Denials], [At Risk Revenue]\n- [Avg Days to Payment], [MTD Claims], [Paid by Payment Date]\n- [Appeal Success Rate], [Total Appeal Recovery]\n\nfact_encounter (use for case-mix / DRG margin questions):\n- [Total Encounters], [Total Charges], [Total Cost], [Avg Cost Per Encounter], [Total Expected Reimbursement]\n- [Avg DRG Weight], [Inpatient Encounters], [Emergency Encounters]\n- [Readmission Rate], [Avg Length of Stay]\n- [PY Charges], [YoY Charge Growth], [YTD Charges]\n\nfact_prescription:\n- [Total Fills], [Total Rx Cost], [Avg Rx Cost Per Fill], [Generic Fill Rate], [Payer Rx Cost], [Patient Copay Total]\n\nfact_diagnosis:\n- [Unique Diagnoses], [Chronic Diagnoses], [Patients with Chronic Conditions]\n\nagg_medication_adherence:\n- [Adherent Rate], [Avg PDC Score]\n\ndim_payer (SCD2 \u00c3\u00a2\u00e2\u201a\u00ac\u00e2\u20ac\u009d measures pre-filter is_active = 1):\n- [Total Payers], [Avg Reimbursement Rate], [Large Network Payers], [Commercial Payers], [Government Payers]\n\ndim_patient (SCD2 \u00c3\u00a2\u00e2\u201a\u00ac\u00e2\u20ac\u009d measures pre-filter is_current = 1):\n- [Total Patients], [Chronic Patients], [Avg Patient Age]\n\nFor agg_appeal_outcomes and agg_days_in_ar (no pre-defined measures yet), use SUM/AVERAGE over their numeric columns:\n- agg_appeal_outcomes: appeal_count, appeal_outcome ('Won'/'Lost'/'Pending'), total_amount_recovered, avg_amount_recovered, by payer_name and denial_reason\n- agg_days_in_ar: days_in_ar_bucket, claim_count, billed_amount, by payer_name and age_bucket ('0-30','31-60','61-90','91-120','120+')\n\n=== DAX PATTERNS ===\n1. Single KPI:               EVALUATE { [Denial Rate] }\n2. Sliced by dimension:       EVALUATE SUMMARIZECOLUMNS(dim_payer[payer_name], \"Rate\", [Denial Rate])\n3. With filter:               EVALUATE CALCULATETABLE(SUMMARIZECOLUMNS(dim_payer[payer_name], \"Risk $\", [At Risk Revenue]), dim_payer[payer_type] = \"Commercial\")\n4. Time-intelligence:         EVALUATE SUMMARIZECOLUMNS(dim_date[year], dim_date[month_name], \"Billed\", [Total Billed], \"Paid\", [Total Paid], \"Collection %\", [Collection Rate])\n5. TopN:                      EVALUATE TOPN(10, SUMMARIZECOLUMNS(dim_payer[payer_name], \"Denial %\", [Denial Rate]), [Denial Rate], DESC)\n\n=== ROUTING TO LAKEHOUSE INSTEAD ===\nFall back to the lh_gold_curated lakehouse (SQL) when:\n- Question needs row-level detail (\"list the 50 highest-dollar denied claims\")\n- Question needs a column not exposed as a measure (e.g., specific denial_reason_codes, claim_number)\n- Question requires a JOIN pattern not pre-baked into model relationships\n- Question references one of the NOT-YET-BACKED tables listed above (and the user confirms a SQL workaround is OK)\n\n=== BENCHMARKS (CFO context) ===\nDenial Rate: <10% is healthy (industry median ~12%) | Collection Rate: >95% target | Days to Payment: <30 days target | Appeal Success Rate: 40-60% typical | Generic Fill Rate: >85% | Readmission Rate: <15%",
  "displayName": "PayerAnalytics",
  "type": "semantic_model",
